24:05.430 --> 24:15.499
And the very next thing that happens in the Gospel of John is some Greeks of all places, some Greeks come.

24:16.661 --> 24:22.386
So Jesus comes to gather all nations, even Romans, even Greeks,

24:23.298 --> 24:25.120
And that's where John goes in the next verse.

24:26.622 --> 24:37.777
In choosing the donkey, Jesus finds the perfect way to say, I am the long expected king, but I am not the king you expect.

24:39.820 --> 24:44.306
You hope for an earthly king to liberate you from an oppressive government.

24:44.947 --> 24:47.090
But Jesus says, yes, I am the king.

24:48.872 --> 24:53.298
But I come not to conjure war against a power so small

24:53.506 --> 25:03.141
is Rome, but to make peace with God Almighty and save my people from their sins forever.

25:04.824 --> 25:10.072
So we come to these waters and we get to experience.

25:10.653 --> 25:15.681
Watch in faith the dramatization of being rescued from our sins.

25:16.142 --> 25:21.170
This is a one-time experience of grace for those in the waters.

25:23.330 --> 25:29.118
And this is an ongoing, repeated experience of grace for us who watch on in faith.

25:30.079 --> 25:35.486
So we don't twiddle our thumbs and watch the clock at a baptism.

25:36.968 --> 25:39.572
We get to hear preaching in the baptism.

25:39.792 --> 25:53.170
Each baptism continues to proclaim, continues to bear witness to us of either what Jesus has done for you or what He will do for you if you'll come to Him in faith.

25:53.506 --> 25:55.189
like those before us here this morning.

25:55.950 --> 25:56.351
Let's pray.

25:58.915 --> 26:04.283
So Father in Heaven, thank You for sending Your Son.

26:06.867 --> 26:11.575
Thank You that He is far more than we expect.

26:13.758 --> 26:21.010
We are such half-hearted creatures, fooling about with such short-sighted and short-lived hopes

26:21.602 --> 26:23.785
We are so far too easily pleased.

26:25.989 --> 26:32.318
And yet in Jesus, you gave us so much more than we could ask for or imagine.

26:33.039 --> 26:40.130
You gave us eternal forgiveness of our sins and reconciliation with you and the joy for which we're made.

26:40.831 --> 26:45.118
So would we enjoy that again as we see it in the waters of baptism?

26:46.520 --> 26:50.706
And if any here come this morning wrestling in unbelief,

26:51.490 --> 26:53.435
Would you give the gift of faith?

26:53.795 --> 26:59.509
Would they trust in Jesus just like these 15 who bear witness before us this morning?

27:00.772 --> 27:01.734
In Jesus' name we pray.

27:03.117 --> 27:03.538
Amen.

